      "note": "Amplitude-weighted mean τ of a biexponential fit (depolarizing/repolarizing voltage steps in HEK cells, voltage clamp, room temp 22-25 °C, n = 4; 561 nm laser, 50 mW/mm²; VARNAM/Kannan 2018 Table S1, which also characterizes FlicR2). Rise: τfast 2.9 ± 0.2 ms, τslow 29.5 ± 2.1 ms → on = 16.2 ms. Decay: τfast 3.1 ± 0.6 ms, τslow 28.5 ± 4.5 ms → off = 15.8 ms. The paper reports only τfast/τslow, NOT the component amplitudes, so a 50:50 fast:slow split is assumed; FlicR2's fast component is ~2.9/3.1 ms if the fast term dominates.",
      "sourceFigure": "Table S1",
      "proofread": false
    }
